  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6573.81 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6575 (2.25B), dealers are actively selling delta into this rally to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with massive positive gamma concentration between 6570-6585 should cap upside momentum and pull price back toward the 6575 anchor, especially given the recent wall break event. Watch for continued dealer selling pressure if we push through 6575, but expect strong mean reversion dynamics to dominate with dealers buying any dips toward the flip strike at 6518.",
